  "prompt": "Which is a suitable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center in Monroe County IL?",
  "response": "Monroe County, IL, has several reputable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab centers. One of the most well-known and highly recommended facilities in the area is:\n\n**Gateway Foundation**  \nGateway Foundation offers evidence-based addiction treatment programs, including inpatient rehab, detox, and outpatient services. While their primary location is not in Monroe County, they have facilities in nearby counties, such as Alton, IL, which is accessible for residents of Monroe County. Gateway Foundation is known for its comprehensive treatment approach, including therapy, counseling, and aftercare planning.\n\nIf you're looking for a facility closer to Monroe County, consider reaching out to:\n\n**Chestnut Health Systems**  \nChestnut Health Systems provides addiction treatment services, including inpatient rehab, in nearby counties. They offer personalized care, including medical detox, counseling, and behavioral therapy.\n\nTo find the most suitable rehab center for your needs, I recommend:\n1. Contacting your insurance provider to verify coverage.\n2. Reaching out to local health departments or addiction helplines for recommendations.\n3. Visiting the **SAMHSA Treatment Locator** (https://findtreatment.samhsa.gov) for a list of certified facilities near Monroe County.\n\nLet me know if you'd like help narrowing down options or accessing additional resources!",
